				<title>Site Criticism Team - Staff Review</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13141613/scp-5591#post-4548213</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 15 Mar 2020 05:12:22 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>TheMightyMcB</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4483018</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>While I will forever have a soft spot in my heart for anything MWDOT-related, I don't think this is a particularly strong piece. There are a few choices that were made here that indicate that things were pretty rushed; specifically the dropping of &quot;SCP-&quot; in the containment procedures and the sort of hammy and on the nose dialogue that moreso explains exactly what is going on here. I think that this <em>could</em> be a good skip, but right now it isn't. -1, but I'm interested in working with you to fix this up after jamcon voting is over if you'll have me.</p> <p><span style="font-size:smaller;"><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> <em>Opinions expressed in this review do not reflect the opinions of SCP Wiki staff as a whole. Please respond to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/themightymcb" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4483018&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1584249141" alt="TheMightyMcB" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4483018)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/themightymcb" >TheMightyMcB</a></span> or contact the captain of the Site Criticism Team, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/soullesssingularity" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=637830&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1584249141" alt="SoullessSingularity" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=637830)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/soullesssingularity" >SoullessSingularity</a></span>, for any questions or concerns relating to this review.</em></span></p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
